ory:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Jamaican emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:People from Kingston, Jamaica]]\n", "name_user": "Cardiffbear88", "label": "safe", "comment": "Remove tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parisa_Fitz-Henley"}
{"title_page": "American Cinema Editors Awards 2013", "text_new": "<div style=\"float: right; font-size: smaller; background-color:#ABCDEF; padding: 12px; margin-left: 5em; margin-bottom: 2em; width: 180px\" align=\"center\">\n\n'''63rd ACE Eddie Awards'''<br>\n<div>\nFebruary 16, 2013\n</div>\n----\nFeature Film (Dramatic): <br>\n<big>'''Argo'''</big>\n----\nFeature Film (Comedy or Musical): <br>\n<big>'''Silver Linings Playbook'''</big>\n</div>\n\nThe '''63rd [[American Cinema Editors]] Eddie Awards''', which were presented on Saturday, February 16, 2013 at the [[Beverly Hilton Hotel]], honored the best [[editor]]s in [[film]]s and [[television]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/american-cinema-editors-announce-63rd-411244 | title=American Cinema Editors Announce 63rd Annual Eddie Award Nominees | work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=January 11, 2013 | accessdate=January 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://deadline.com/2013/02/63rd-annual-ace-eddie-award-2013-film-editors-432761/ | title=ACE Eddie Awards: 'Argo', 'Silver Linings Playbook', 'Brave'; TV 'Breaking Bad', 'The Newsroom', 'Hemingway & Gellhorn' | website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] | date=February 16, 2013 | accessdate=January 6, 2015}}</ref>\n\nNominees were announced on January 16, 2013.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n\n===Film===\n'''Best Edited Feature Film \u2013 Dramatic:'''\n\n'''[[William Goldenberg]] - ''[[Argo (2012 film)|Argo]]'''''\n*[[Tim Squyres]] - ''[[Life of Pi (film)|Life of Pi]]''\n*[[Michael Kahn (film editor)|Michael Kahn]] - ''[[Lincoln (film)|Lincoln]]''\n*[[Stuart Baird]] - ''[[Skyfall]]''\n*[[Dylan Tichenor]] and [[William Goldenberg]] - ''[[Zero Dark Thirty]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Feature Film \u2013 Comedy or Musical:'''\n\n'''[[Jay Cassidy]] and [[Crispin Struthers]] - ''[[Silver Linings Playbook]]'''''\n*[[Chris Gill]] - ''[[The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel]]''\n*[[Melanie Ann Oliver]] and [[Chris Dickens]] - ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''\n*[[Andrew Weisblum]] - ''[[Moonrise Kingdom]]''\n*[[Jeff Freeman]] - ''[[Ted (film)|Ted]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Animated Feature Film:'''\n\n'''[[Nicolas C. Smith]] - ''[[Brave (2012 film)|Brave]]'''''\n*[[Chris Lebenzon]] and [[Mark Solomon (editor)|Mark Solomon]] - ''[[Frankenweenie (2012 film)|Frankenweenie]]''\n*[[Joyce Arrastia]] - ''[[Rise of the Guardians]]''\n*[[Tim Mertens (film editor)|Tim Mertens]] - ''[[Wreck-It Ralph]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Documentary (Feature):'''\n\n'''[[Malik Bendjelloul]] - ''[[Searching for Sugar Man]]'''''\n*[[Ron Fricke]] and [[Mark Magidson]] - ''[[Samsara (2011 film)|Samsara]]''\n*[[Billy McMillin]] - ''[[West of Memphis]]''\n\n===Television===\n'''Best Edited Half-Hour Series for Television:'''\n\n'''[[Gary Levy (editor)|Gary Levy]] - ''[[Nurse Jackie]]'' for \"Handle Your Scandal\"'''\n*[[Robert Frazen]] and [[Catherine Haight]] - ''[[Girls (TV Series)|Girls]]'' for \"Pilot\"\n*[[Ryan Case]] - ''[[Modern Family]]'' for \"Mystery Date\"\n\n'''Best Edited One-Hour Series \u2013 Commercial Television:'''\n\n'''[[Skip Macdonald]] - ''[[Breaking Bad]]'' for \"Dead Freight\"'''\n*[[Kelley Dixon]] - ''[[Breaking Bad]]'' for \"Gliding Over All\"\n*[[Tom Wilson (film editor)|Tom Wilson]] - ''[[Mad Men]]'' for \"The Other Woman\"\n*[[Keith Henderson (film editor)|Keith Henderson]] - ''[[Nashville]]'' for \"Pilot\"\n*[[Andrew Weisblum]] - ''[[Smash (U.S. TV series)|Smash]]'' for \"Pilot\"\n\n'''Best Edited One-Hour Series \u2013 Non-Commercial Television:'''\n\n'''[[Anne McCabe]] - ''[[The Newsroom (U.S. TV series)|The Newsroom]]'' for ''We Just Decided To (Pilot)'''''\n*[[Terry Kelley]] - ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'' for ''The Choice''\n*[[Jordan Goldman (editor)|Jordan Goldman]] - ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'' for ''State of Independence''\n\n'''Best Edited Miniseries or Film \u2013 Commercial Television:'''\n\n'''[[Lucia Zucchetti]] - ''[[Game Change (film)|Game Change]]'''''\n*[[Don Cassidy]] - ''[[Hatfields & McCoys (miniseries)|Hatfields & McCoys]] Part 1''\n*[[Walter Murch]] - ''[[Hemingway & Gellhorn]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Non-Scripted Series:'''\n\n'''[[Andy Netley]] and [[Sharon Gillooly]] - ''[[Frozen Planet]]'' for \"Ends Of The Earth\"'''\n\n'''Student Competition:'''\n\n'''Michael Smith \u2013 ''[[American Film Institute|AFI]]'''''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000017/2013 ACE Award 2013] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]\n\n{{ACE Awards Chron}}\n\n[[Category:American Cinema Editors]]\n[[Category:American film awards]]\n[[Category:2013 film awards]]\n[[Category:2013 guild awards]]\n[[Category:Film editing awards]]\n[[Category:2013 in American cinema]]\n", "text_old": "<div style=\"float: right; font-size: smaller; background-color:#ABCDEF; padding: 12px; margin-left: 5em; margin-bottom: 2em; width: 180px\" align=\"center\">\n\n'''63rd ACE Eddie Awards'''<br>\n<div>\nFebruary 16, 2013\n</div>\n----\nFeature Film (Dramatic): <br>\n<big>'''Argo'''</big>\n----\nFeature Film (Comedy or Musical): <br>\n<big>'''Silver Linings Playbook'''</big>\n</div>\n\nThe '''63rd [[American Cinema Editors]] Eddie Awards''', which were presented on Saturday, February 16, 2013 at the [[Beverly Hilton Hotel]], honored the best [[editor]]s in [[film]]s and [[television]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/american-cinema-editors-announce-63rd-411244 | title=American Cinema Editors Announce 63rd Annual Eddie Award Nominees | work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=January 11, 2013 | accessdate=January 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://deadline.com/2013/02/63rd-annual-ace-eddie-award-2013-film-editors-432761/ | title=ACE Eddie Awards: 'Argo', 'Silver Linings Playbook', 'Brave'; TV 'Breaking Bad', 'The Newsroom', 'Hemingway & Gellhorn' | website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] | date=February 16, 2013 | accessdate=January 6, 2015}}</ref>\n\nNominees were announced on January 16, 2013.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n\n===Film===\n'''Best Edited Feature Film \u2013 Dramatic:'''\n\n'''[[William Goldenberg]] - ''[[Argo (2012 film)|Argo]]'''''\n*[[Tim Squyres]] - ''[[Life of Pi (film)|Life of Pi]]''\n*[[Michael Kahn (film editor)|Michael Kahn]] - ''[[Lincoln (film)|Lincoln]]''\n*[[Stuart Baird]] - ''[[Skyfall]]''\n*[[Dylan Tichenor]] and [[William Goldenberg]] - ''[[Zero Dark Thirty]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Feature Film \u2013 Comedy or Musical:'''\n\n'''[[Jay Cassidy]] and [[Crispin Struthers]] - ''[[Silver Linings Playbook]]'''''\n*[[Chris Gill]] - ''[[The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel]]''\n*[[Melanie Ann Oliver]] and [[Chris Dickens]] - ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''\n*[[Andrew Weisblum]] - ''[[Moonrise Kingdom]]''\n*[[Jeff Freeman]] - ''[[Ted (film)|Ted]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Animated Feature Film:'''\n\n'''[[Nicolas C. Smith]] - ''[[Brave (2012 film)|Brave]]'''''\n*[[Chris Lebenzon]] and [[Mark Solomon (editor)|Mark Solomon]] - ''[[Frankenweenie (2012 film)|Frankenweenie]]''\n*[[Joyce Arrastia]] - ''[[Rise of the Guardians]]''\n*[[Tim Mertens (film editor)|Tim Mertens]] - ''[[Wreck-It Ralph]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Documentary (Feature):'''\n\n'''[[Malik Bendjelloul]] - ''[[Searching for Sugar Man]]'''''\n*[[Ron Fricke]] and [[Mark Magidson]] - ''[[Samsara (2011 film)|Samsara]]''\n*[[Billy McMillin]] - ''[[West of Memphis]]''\n\n===Television===\n'''Best Edited Half-Hour Series for Television:'''\n\n'''[[Gary Levy (editor)|Gary Levy]] - ''[[Nurse Jackie]]'' for \"Handle Your Scandal\"\n*[[Robert Frazen]] and [[Catherine Haight]] - ''[[Girls (TV Series)|Girls]]'' for \"Pilot\"\n*[[Ryan Case]] - ''[[Modern Family]]'' for \"Mystery Date\"\n\n'''Best Edited One-Hour Series \u2013 Commercial Television:'''\n\n'''[[Skip Macdonald]] - ''[[Breaking Bad]]'' for \"Dead Freight\"'''\n*[[Kelley Dixon]] - ''[[Breaking Bad]]'' for \"Gliding Over All\"\n*[[Tom Wilson (film editor)|Tom Wilson]] - ''[[Mad Men]]'' for \"The Other Woman\"\n*[[Keith Henderson (film editor)|Keith Henderson]] - ''[[Nashville]]'' for \"Pilot\"\n*[[Andrew Weisblum]] - ''[[Smash (U.S. TV series)|Smash]]'' for \"Pilot\"\n\n'''Best Edited One-Hour Series \u2013 Non-Commercial Television:'''\n\n'''[[Anne McCabe]] - ''[[The Newsroom (U.S. TV series)|The Newsroom]] for ''We Just Decided To (Pilot)'''''\n*[[Terry Kelley]] - ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'' for ''The Choice''\n*[[Jordan Goldman (editor)|Jordan Goldman]] - ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'' for ''State of Independence''\n\n'''Best Edited Miniseries or Film \u2013 Commercial Television:'''\n\n'''[[Lucia Zucchetti]] - ''[[Game Change (film)|Game Change]]'''''\n*[[Don Cassidy]] - ''[[Hatfields & McCoys (miniseries)|Hatfields & McCoys]] Part 1''\n*[[Walter Murch]] - ''[[Hemingway & Gellhorn]]''\n\n'''Best Edited Non-Scripted Series:'''\n\n'''[[Andy Netley]] and [[Sharon Gillooly]] - ''[[Frozen Planet]]'' for \"Ends Of The Earth\"'''\n\n'''Student Competition:'''\n\n'''Michael Smith \u2013 ''[[American Film Institute|AFI]]'''''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000017/2013 ACE Award 2013] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]\n\n{{ACE Awards Chron}}\n\n[[Category:American Cinema Editors]]\n[[Category:American film awards]]\n[[Category:2013 film awards]]\n[[Category:2013 guild awards]]\n[[Category:Film editing awards]]\n[[Category:2013 in American cinema]]\n", "name_user": "WOSlinker", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix bold/italics", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Cinema_Editors_Awards_2013"}
{"title_page": "\u00c9lodie Lorandi", "text_new": "{{short description|French Paralympic swimmer}}\n\n'''\u00c9lodie Lorandi''' (born 31 May 1989, in [[Cannes]]) is a French Paralympic swimmer who won silver at the [[2008 Summer Paralympics]] in  the 200m individual medley SM10. She expressed hopes of winning gold at the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]],<ref>[http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/lib/TheASP.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=514&personid=689309 IPC bio]</ref> which she did at the Women's 400m Freestyle - S10.<ref>[http://www.london2012.com/paralympics/athlete/lorandi-elodie-5509155/index.html London 2012 page]</ref>\n\nOn 1 January 2013, Lorandi was made a Knight (Chevalier) of the [[L\u00e9gion d'honneur]].<ref>[http://www.nicematin.com/derniere-minute/legion-dhonneur-aschieri-muffat-et-agnel-dans-la-promo-du-1er-janvier.1099542.html L\u00e9gion d'Honneur: Aschieri, Muffat et Agnel dans la promo du 1er janvier] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927144042/http://www.nicematin.com/derniere-minute/legion-dhonneur-aschieri-muffat-et-agnel-dans-la-promo-du-1er-janvier.1099542.html# |date=2013-09-27 }} - nicematin.com</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=elodie-lorandi|old_id=689309|name=Elodie Lorandi}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lorandi, Elodie}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Chevaliers of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:French female swimmers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Paralympic swimmers of France]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Cannes]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:S10-classified Paralympic swimmers]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games gold medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in swimming]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2018 Mediterranean Games]]\n\n\n{{France-swimming-bio-stub}}\n{{France-Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French Paralympic swimmer}}\n'''\u00c9lodie Lorandi''' (born 31 May 1989, in [[Cannes]]) is a French Paralympic swimmer who won silver at the [[2008 Summer Paralympics]] in  the 200m individual medley SM10. She expressed hopes of winning gold at the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]],<ref>[http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/lib/TheASP.asp?pageid=8937&sportid=514&personid=689309 IPC bio]</ref> which she did at the Women's 400m Freestyle - S10.<ref>[http://www.london2012.com/paralympics/athlete/lorandi-elodie-5509155/index.html London 2012 page]</ref>\n\nOn 1 January 2013, Lorandi was made a Knight (Chevalier) of the [[L\u00e9gion d'honneur]].<ref>[http://www.nicematin.com/derniere-minute/legion-dhonneur-aschieri-muffat-et-agnel-dans-la-promo-du-1er-janvier.1099542.html L\u00e9gion d'Honneur: Aschieri, Muffat et Agnel dans la promo du 1er janvier] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927144042/http://www.nicematin.com/derniere-minute/legion-dhonneur-aschieri-muffat-et-agnel-dans-la-promo-du-1er-janvier.1099542.html# |date=2013-09-27 }} - nicematin.com</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IPC athlete|689309}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lorandi, Elodie}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Chevaliers of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n[[Category:French female swimmers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for France]]\n[[Category:Paralympic swimmers of France]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Cannes]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Swimmers at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:S10-classified Paralympic swimmers]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games gold medalists for France]]\